parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the basement storage door latches can cause the doors to open while traveling, potentially leading to accidents, traffic hazards, and damage to the vehicle or other property.
symptoms: The basement storage doors open unexpectedly while driving
and can swing open into traffic lanes
causing potential hazards to other vehicles
or cyclists. The doors may also cause damage to the vehicle itself or surrounding objects.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The compartment doors opening while driving can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities to pedestrians and other road users, as well as damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: posing a risk to pedestrians and other road users.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unstable bed system can cause the bed to fall and strike the driver's head while in motion, leading to serious injury or fatality.
symptoms: The bed above the driver and passenger seats does not lock in place on the passenger side
and the seatbelt-type latch on the driver's side cannot be secured
putting additional stress on the driver-side motor drive
which can lead to breakage and bed collapse.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The improper routing of the propane line for the Truma Water Heater can cause the line to be pinched and crushed, leading to a potential propane leak, explosion, or fire hazard, putting the occupants of the vehicle at risk.
symptoms: Water heater not providing enough hot water
burner cycling on and off or not staying lit
reduced propane flow (3-6 WC) after initial startup.
